B7CUI","Q7DDNWD6",[219,220,221,22,26,30,222,223,224,225,223,226,105],"isic000396","i.sicily inscription 000396",{"_":5},"catina","catania","sicilia","sicily","latin",[],{"title":229,"body":230,"divs":231,"editions":256,"images":266,"handnote":272},"ISic000396. I.Sicily inscription 000396","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Crescentiae\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Crescentiae\">Crescentiae\u003C/span>\u003C/span> bene m[e]renti \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>in pace &lt;quae&gt; vixit ann(is) \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>p(lus) m(i)n(us) L deposit(a) III Kal(endas) \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>Decemb(res) F̣ḷ(avio) Ṣṭịḷịc̣ọ-\u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ne cons(ule) se vivi conpa[ra-]\u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>[v]er[u]n[t] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.2 quae\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Crescentiae\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Crescentiae\">CRESCENTIAE\u003C/span>\u003C/span>BENEM[.]RENTI\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>INPACEQUEVIXITANN\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>PMNLDEPOSITIIIKAL\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>DECEMB.........\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>NECONSSEVIVICONPA[..]\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>[.]ER[.]N[.]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.2 quae\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000396_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic000396_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000396.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic000396-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of CIL, amended by Ferrua\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"4\">4: \u003Cspan>Amico read a confused sequence of letters after DECEMB, and conjectured FL.STILICO, and Ferrua concurs; Mommsen instead proposed FL.OPILIO\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>If Mommsen's reading of line 4 is accepted, the date is either 453 or 521 CE. Ferrua notes that Stilicho was also consul II in 405, but the absence of indication of iteration leads him to prefer 400 CE.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003C